OL,5,Cguard
OL,7,FIt added: "He had also expressed a
OL,8,Fdesire to apologise. The sub-panel
OL,9,Faccepted Mr Anderson's evidence that
OL,10,Fhe had faced 'challenging personal
OL,11,Fcircumstances' on the day in question
OL,12,Fand his 'unacceptable behaviour' was
OL,13,F'not planned or premeditated'."
OL,15,FIn its findings, the watchdog
OL,16,Fhighlighted the "power imbalance"
OL,17,Fbetween the prominent MP and the
OL,18,Fsecurity officer and noted the
OL,19,Fimportance laid out in Parliament's
OL,20,Fbehaviour code not to "abuse" his
OL,21,Finfluence or authority.
